extChoiceId":32,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","QuestionID":"QID1721185797"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185798","SecondaryAttribute":"Thank you, you have qualified for the study.\u00a0 In the following sections, we\u2019re interested in your","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Thank you, you have qualified for the study.&nbsp;<br \/>\n<br \/>\nIn the following sections, we&rsquo;re interested in your opinion about climate change and climate scientists.&nbsp;<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<strong>Climate scientists study changes in the Earth&#39;s climate over time and how they might affect the planet in the future.<\/strong> Please keep this definition in mind when filling out this study.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nPlease make sure you do not close this tab until you have finished the study. You must complete the whole study to collect your payment.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Transition","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Thank you, you have qualified for the study.\u00a0 In the following sections, we\u2019re interested in your...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Thank you, you have qualified for the study.&nbsp;<br \/>\n<br \/>\nIn the following sections, we&rsquo;re interested in your opinion about climate change and climate scientists.&nbsp;<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<strong>Climate scientists study changes in the Earth&#39;s climate over time and how they might affect the planet in the future.<\/strong> Please keep this definition in mind when filling out this study.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nPlease make sure you do not close this tab until you have finished the study. You must complete the whole study to collect your payment.","QuestionID":"QID1721185798"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185799","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"transition1_time","QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":"0","MaxSeconds":"0"},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":24,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","QuestionID":"QID1721185799"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185800","SecondaryAttribute":"You are now moving on to the final section of the study. Please answer the following questions to...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"You are now moving on to the final section of the study.<br><br>Please answer the following questions to the best of your ability.<br><br>Thank you.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Transition3","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"You are now moving on to the final section of the study. Please answer the following questions to...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"You are now moving on to the final section of the study.<br><br>Please answer the following questions to the best of your ability.<br><br>Thank you.","QuestionID":"QID1721185800"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185801","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Transition3_Time","QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":"0","MaxSeconds":"0"},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":20,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","QuestionID":"QID1721185801"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185802","SecondaryAttribute":"The History of Neckties Neckties date back hundreds of years, coming into existence as the direct...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-f617683e-7fff-d029-e0c5-a07bbbbd6ee0\">The History of Neckties<\/b><\/p>\n<br \/>\nNeckties date back hundreds of years, coming into existence as the direct result of a war. In 1660, in celebration of its hard-fought victory over the Ottoman Empire, a regiment from Croatia (then part of the Habsburg Monarchy) visited Paris. The soldiers were presented as heroes to Louis XIV, a monarch well known for his tendency toward personal adornment. The officers of this regiment were wearing brightly colored handkerchiefs fashioned of silk around their necks. These neck cloths - which probably descended from the Roman fascalia worn by orators to warm the vocal chords - struck the fancy of the king, and he soon made them an insignia of royalty as he created a regiment of Royal Cravattes. Vanity reigns supreme. The word &quot;cravat,&quot; is derived from the word &quot;Croat.&quot;<br \/>\n<br \/>\nIt wasn&#39;t long before this new style crossed the channel to England. Soon, no gentleman would have considered himself well-dressed without sporting some sort of cloth around his neck-the more decorative, the better. At times, cravats were worn so high that a man could not move his head without turning his whole body. There were even reports of cravats worn so thick that they stopped sword thrusts. The various styles knew no bounds, as cravats of tasseled strings, plaid scarves, tufts and bows of ribbon, lace and embroidered linen all had their staunch adherents.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nHow can we account for the continued popularity of neckties? For years, fashion historians and sociologists predicted their demise - the one element of a man&#39;s attire with no obvious function. Perhaps they are merely part of an inherited tradition. As long as world leaders continue to wear ties, the youth of the world will follow suit and ties will remain a key component to any man&#39;s professional wardrobe.&nbsp;Moreover, the adaptability of neckties to various styles and occasions ensures their enduring relevance in the ever-evolving landscape of men&#39;s fashion.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"stimulus","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The History of Neckties Neckties date back hundreds of years, coming into existence as the direct...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-f617683e-7fff-d029-e0c5-a07bbbbd6ee0\">The History of Neckties<\/b><\/p>\n<br \/>\nNeckties date back hundreds of years, coming into existence as the direct result of a war. In 1660, in celebration of its hard-fought victory over the Ottoman Empire, a regiment from Croatia (then part of the Habsburg Monarchy) visited Paris. The soldiers were presented as heroes to Louis XIV, a monarch well known for his tendency toward personal adornment. The officers of this regiment were wearing brightly colored handkerchiefs fashioned of silk around their necks. These neck cloths - which probably descended from the Roman fascalia worn by orators to warm the vocal chords - struck the fancy of the king, and he soon made them an insignia of royalty as he created a regiment of Royal Cravattes. Vanity reigns supreme. The word &quot;cravat,&quot; is derived from the word &quot;Croat.&quot;<br \/>\n<br \/>\nIt wasn&#39;t long before this new style crossed the channel to England. Soon, no gentleman would have considered himself well-dressed without sporting some sort of cloth around his neck-the more decorative, the better. At times, cravats were worn so high that a man could not move his head without turning his whole body. There were even reports of cravats worn so thick that they stopped sword thrusts. The various styles knew no bounds, as cravats of tasseled strings, plaid scarves, tufts and bows of ribbon, lace and embroidered linen all had their staunch adherents.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nHow can we account for the continued popularity of neckties? For years, fashion historians and sociologists predicted their demise - the one element of a man&#39;s attire with no obvious function. Perhaps they are merely part of an inherited tradition. As long as world leaders continue to wear ties, the youth of the world will follow suit and ties will remain a key component to any man&#39;s professional wardrobe.&nbsp;Moreover, the adaptability of neckties to various styles and occasions ensures their enduring relevance in the ever-evolving landscape of men&#39;s fashion.","QuestionID":"QID1721185802"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185803","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"control_ties_time","QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":"0","MaxSeconds":"0"},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":60,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","QuestionID":"QID1721185803"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185804","SecondaryAttribute":"The Rules of Baseball \u00a0 Baseball, a quintessential American pastime, is a sport rooted in traditi..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d5cdc32-7fff-f906-3d44-2802ee6c9989\">The Rules of Baseball<\/b><\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Baseball, a quintessential American pastime, is a sport rooted in tradition and governed by a set of rules that define its unique charm. Understanding these rules is essential to fully appreciate the game.<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">At its core, baseball consists of two teams, each aiming to score more runs than their opponent. The game unfolds over nine innings, with each team taking turns at bat and in the field. The offensive team strives to hit the ball thrown by the pitcher and advance around a series of bases, while the defensive team aims to record outs by catching the ball or tagging runners.<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Key rules in baseball include the three-strike rule, which requires a batter to either hit the ball or accumulate three strikes to be called out, and the four-ball rule, granting a batter a free walk to first base if the pitcher throws four balls outside the strike zone. Additionally, there are regulations governing fair and foul balls, baserunning, fielding, and pitching techniques. Baseball&#39;s rules ensure fairness, strategy, and thrilling moments, making it a captivating and beloved sport cherished by fans worldwide.<br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Moreover, baseball&#39;s rich history and cultural significance have led to the development of various traditions and rituals that further enhance the game-day experience. From the ceremonial first pitch to the seventh-inning stretch, fans eagerly participate in these time-honored customs, adding to the atmosphere of camaraderie and excitement in stadiums across the country. These traditions not only connect fans to the sport&#39;s past but also contribute to the sense of community and shared identity among baseball enthusiasts.<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The ups and downs of a baseball game mirror life&rsquo;s challenges and triumphs, reminding us to stay resilient in the face of adversity and to celebrate our successes with humility. Through its timeless appeal, baseball continues to inspire generations, fostering a sense of unity and shared passion that transcends boundaries.<\/p>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The Rules of Baseball \u00a0 Baseball, a quintessential American pastime, is a sport rooted in traditi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d5cdc32-7fff-f906-3d44-2802ee6c9989\">The Rules of Baseball<\/b><\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Baseball, a quintessential American pastime, is a sport rooted in tradition and governed by a set of rules that define its unique charm. Understanding these rules is essential to fully appreciate the game.<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">At its core, baseball consists of two teams, each aiming to score more runs than their opponent. The game unfolds over nine innings, with each team taking turns at bat and in the field. The offensive team strives to hit the ball thrown by the pitcher and advance around a series of bases, while the defensive team aims to record outs by catching the ball or tagging runners.<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Key rules in baseball include the three-strike rule, which requires a batter to either hit the ball or accumulate three strikes to be called out, and the four-ball rule, granting a batter a free walk to first base if the pitcher throws four balls outside the strike zone. Additionally, there are regulations governing fair and foul balls, baserunning, fielding, and pitching techniques. Baseball&#39;s rules ensure fairness, strategy, and thrilling moments, making it a captivating and beloved sport cherished by fans worldwide.<br \/>\n&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Moreover, baseball&#39;s rich history and cultural significance have led to the development of various traditions and rituals that further enhance the game-day experience. From the ceremonial first pitch to the seventh-inning stretch, fans eagerly participate in these time-honored customs, adding to the atmosphere of camaraderie and excitement in stadiums across the country. These traditions not only connect fans to the sport&#39;s past but also contribute to the sense of community and shared identity among baseball enthusiasts.<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The ups and downs of a baseball game mirror life&rsquo;s challenges and triumphs, reminding us to stay resilient in the face of adversity and to celebrate our successes with humility. Through its timeless appeal, baseball continues to inspire generations, fostering a sense of unity and shared passion that transcends boundaries.<\/p>","DataExportTag":" ","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionID":"QID1721185804"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185805","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"control_ball_time","QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":"0","MaxSeconds":"0"},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":52,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","QuestionID":"QID1721185805"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185806","SecondaryAttribute":"Different Types of Dances Dance, a universal form of expression, encompasses a diverse array of s...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-cfbd5dfa-7fff-009c-0d2e-dc699e9f8517\">Different Types of Dances<\/b><\/p>\n<br \/>\nDance, a universal form of expression, encompasses a diverse array of styles and traditions, each brimming with unique characteristics and cultural significance. From the refined movements of classical ballet to the vivacious rhythms of Latin dances and the dynamic energy of hip-hop, the world of dance offers a rich tapestry of experiences for enthusiasts of all backgrounds.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nClassical ballet, with its graceful movements and precise technique, epitomizes elegance and storytelling, with iconic productions like Swan Lake and The Nutcracker captivating audiences worldwide. On the other hand, contemporary dance thrives on innovation and fluidity, blending elements from various styles to create cutting-edge choreography that challenges conventional boundaries.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nLatin dances such as salsa, tango, and samba exude the passionate spirit and infectious joy of Latin American cultures, fostering connections and celebrations through movement and music. Meanwhile, hip-hop, rooted in African-American and urban communities, pulsates with its high-energy performances and expressive gestures, encompassing a wide range of styles from breaking to popping and locking.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nBeyond these well-known genres, ballroom, jazz, tap, and folk dances each boast their own rich heritage and artistic nuances, while contemporary cultural dances continue to evolve and reflect the ever-changing global landscape.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nIn essence, the diverse world of dance serves as a canvas for human expression, allowing dancers to convey emotions, tell stories, and forge connections with audiences in deeply resonant ways.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nThrough its universal language, dance transcends cultural barriers, uniting people of different backgrounds and fostering understanding and appreciation for our shared humanity. It stands as a testament to the enduring power of creativity and connection in our world. Dance serves as a bridge between generations, preserving heritage while also embracing innovation and evolution. Moreover, it offers individuals a form of self-expression and liberation, allowing them to communicate emotions and experiences beyond words. As such, dance has the potential to inspire, uplift, and transform both individuals and communities.","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Different Types of Dances Dance, a universal form of expression, encompasses a diverse array of s...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-cfbd5dfa-7fff-009c-0d2e-dc699e9f8517\">Different Types of Dances<\/b><\/p>\n<br \/>\nDance, a universal form of expression, encompasses a diverse array of styles and traditions, each brimming with unique characteristics and cultural significance. From the refined movements of classical ballet to the vivacious rhythms of Latin dances and the dynamic energy of hip-hop, the world of dance offers a rich tapestry of experiences for enthusiasts of all backgrounds.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nClassical ballet, with its graceful movements and precise technique, epitomizes elegance and storytelling, with iconic productions like Swan Lake and The Nutcracker captivating audiences worldwide. On the other hand, contemporary dance thrives on innovation and fluidity, blending elements from various styles to create cutting-edge choreography that challenges conventional boundaries.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nLatin dances such as salsa, tango, and samba exude the passionate spirit and infectious joy of Latin American cultures, fostering connections and celebrations through movement and music. Meanwhile, hip-hop, rooted in African-American and urban communities, pulsates with its high-energy performances and expressive gestures, encompassing a wide range of styles from breaking to popping and locking.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nBeyond these well-known genres, ballroom, jazz, tap, and folk dances each boast their own rich heritage and artistic nuances, while contemporary cultural dances continue to evolve and reflect the ever-changing global landscape.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nIn essence, the diverse world of dance serves as a canvas for human expression, allowing dancers to convey emotions, tell stories, and forge connections with audiences in deeply resonant ways.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nThrough its universal language, dance transcends cultural barriers, uniting people of different backgrounds and fostering understanding and appreciation for our shared humanity. It stands as a testament to the enduring power of creativity and connection in our world. Dance serves as a bridge between generations, preserving heritage while also embracing innovation and evolution. Moreover, it offers individuals a form of self-expression and liberation, allowing them to communicate emotions and experiences beyond words. As such, dance has the potential to inspire, uplift, and transform both individuals and communities.","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"DataExportTag":"stimulus","QuestionID":"QID1721185806"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185807","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"control_dance_time","QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":"0","MaxSeconds":"0"},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":36,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","QuestionID":"QID1721185807"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185808","SecondaryAttribute":"You are now moving on to a different section of the study. Please pay close attention to the info...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"You are now moving on to a different section of the study.<br><br>Please pay close attention to the information you will be provided.<br><br>Thank you.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"transition2","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"You are now moving on to a different section of the study. Please pay close attention to the info...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"You are now moving on to a different section of the study.<br><br>Please pay close attention to the information you will be provided.<br><br>Thank you.","QuestionID":"QID1721185808"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185809","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"transition2_time","QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":"0","MaxSeconds":"0"},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":24,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Timing","QuestionID":"QID1721185809"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185810","SecondaryAttribute":"Please indicate your views on the following questions. Answer options below range from 0 to 100....","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please indicate your views on the following questions.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:13px;\">Answer options below range from 0 to 100. Click on any space within this range and a bar will appear. Feel free to move that bar around to the number that best represents your answer.<\/span>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"concern","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please indicate your views on the following questions. Answer options below range from 0 to 100....","ChoiceOrder":["4","5","6","7","8"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Please indicate your views on the following questions.<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:13px;\">Answer options below range from 0 to 100. Click on any space within this range and a bar will appear. Feel free to move that bar around to the number that best represents your answer.<\/span>","QuestionID":"QID1721185810"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185811","SecondaryAttribute":"How concerned are you about climate change?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"How concerned are you about climate change?","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HBAR","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":10,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":true,"CustomStart":true,"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0}},"QuestionDescription":"How concerned are you about climate change?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"&nbsp;"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Extremely"}},"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"How concerned are you about climate change?","DataExportTag":"concern_1","QuestionID":"QID1721185811"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185812","SecondaryAttribute":"How serious a problem is climate change?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"How serious a problem is climate change?","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HBAR","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":10,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":true,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"How serious a problem is climate change?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"&nbsp;"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Extremely"}},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"How serious a problem is climate change?","DataExportTag":"concern_2","QuestionID":"QID1721185812"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185813","SecondaryAttribute":"Relative to other issues facing the US, how important is climate change?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Relative to other issues facing the US, how important is climate change?","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HBAR","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":10,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":true,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Relative to other issues facing the US, how important is climate change?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"&nbsp;"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"RequestResponse","ForceResponseType":"RequestResponse","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"The least important issue"},"2":{"Display":"The most important issue"}},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Relative to other issues facing the US, how important is climate change?","DataExportTag":"concern_3","QuestionID":"QID1721185813"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_b2ULL6XxhpfseDY","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1721185814","SecondaryAttribute":"Timing","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Timing","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Timing","Selector":"PageTimer","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","MinSeconds":"0","MaxSeconds":"0"},"QuestionDescription":"Timing","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"First Click"},"2":{"Display":"Last Click"},"3":{"Display":"Page Submit"},"4":{"Display":"Click Count"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":72,"NextAnswerId":1,"DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"QuestionText_U